title: Sloane‚Äôs
text:
Menu is a bit "limited", but I got the steak and potatoes, and it has definitely surpassed my expectations. Portions were definitely enough for me.

Steak, I'd give a solid 7.5, maybe 8/10. Good texture. Good taste. Very good. Would recommend.

Mashed Potatoes, I've had a lot of places that had very mediocre mashed potatoes where I would just leave it on my plate, but these mashed potatoes with the gravy were pretty good and I finished all of it. Perfect amount of gravy for the mashed potatoes, too. 7-7.5/10.

Carrots, I'm not a fan of carrots generally speaking. For carrots, these were good. Like 6/10 above average good. But the entire time I was eating the carrots, I just thought to myself, "I wish these were sweet potatoes... but maybe that's just too much potato in the entree".

Adding this place to my mental list of "places to go to for a good steak". I'm definitely going to have my family and friends try this place to get their opinions as well as try their other dishes.

title: Dragon Chef
text:
So I order using the online menu, and I‚Äôm appalled that when I picked up my order, it was $10 more than the online menu indicated.  I order 1 dinner (fried rice/2 appetizers) and small side order of Peking Ravioli (total of 4).  Cost of $24.40.  I could have splurged on Chipotle for far less and much better food.  I mentioned to the female cashier about the discrepancies of the online menu and she immediately became defensive, explaining that the online menu had been updated.  I responded that obviously some advertisers did not get the memo. She persisted to the point where I said, look, it is what it is. You haven‚Äôt informed your public and that‚Äôs on you. She blamed her boss and said she‚Äôd inform him.  I doubt I‚Äôm the only person who‚Äôd experienced surprise, and the first time she said she‚Äôd tell her boss.  I‚Äôd guess the next time she tells her boss WILL BE THE FIRST TIME though.

The food?  I‚Äô‚Äôm from Roslindale and patronized this same business since 1980 or so when it opened. Original manager was fabulous. You went in, he knew what you wanted, we talked baseball the whole time, he was a huge fan. The neighborhood owned him. He was one of us. Always the tastiest food.  Today I ordered Kung Pao extra spicy, Egg Roll, and Peking Ravioli side.  Fried rice was part of the dinner component.  I‚Äôve never tasted Kung Pao Chicken so tasteless.  Spicy?  Milk has more zest to it than this slop. And it didn‚Äôt look like a good quality dish, chicken, vegetable, etc. no peanuts which always is part of the dish. Sub par as to appetizing view. Terrible food. Egg Roll was ok. Peking‚Äôs, nothing to stop in or go out of your way for.

Being a customer of this place for over 40 years?  No more.  Done.  There are plenty of Chinese food restaurants right there in Rossie Square.  I‚Äôll give them a try.  I hope this review provides you with some forwarded insight.

Caveat Emptor.

title: Shaking Seafood (Roslindale)
text:
I recently dined at this restaurant, and unfortunately, it was a complete letdown. From start to finish, the service was appalling and left a sour taste in my mouth.

Upon entering, there was no warm welcome or acknowledgment from the staff. We had to wait for what felt like an eternity before anyone bothered to seat us, despite the restaurant being nearly empty.

Once seated, the wait for our orders was excruciatingly long. It took ages for a server to even come to our table to take our drink orders, and when they finally did, they seemed disinterested and unfriendly.

When the food finally arrived, it was subpar at best. The dishes were lukewarm, indicating they had been sitting out for some time before being served. Not to mention, the presentation was sloppy, and it was evident that little care went into preparing our meals.

To make matters worse, when we tried to address our concerns with the manager, they were dismissive and unapologetic. Instead of acknowledging our dissatisfaction, they brushed us off and seemed uninterested in resolving the issues.

Overall, my experience at Shaking Seafood Restaurant was incredibly disappointing. The lackluster service, mediocre food quality, and indifferent management left me feeling frustrated and unlikely to return. Save yourself the hassle and choose a different dining option.

text: If I could give this place ZERO stars I would! The guy at the counter doesn't speak clearly. title: Lala Caribbean restaurant
text:
I googled Haitian restaurants nearby and spotted this one. I parked my car and said hmmmm this is a tiny place‚Ä¶hey let me try it anyways. I went in and the gentlemen behind the counter was so professional and kind. I‚Äôve complimented him because in my opinion it is very hard to find an all around great Haitian restaurant or Haitian food business. I came in and didn‚Äôt know what I wanted. He walked me through making up my mind. He had patience, a great tone of voice, honesty, great listening skills and such a positive energy. This is exactly what ANY restaurant should be like.

The food was amazing - GREAT PORTION ‚≠êÔ∏è I ordered du ri jon jon ( black rice - most people call it but the correct name is dried mushroom rice ) with legumes and baked macaroni and Soup Joumou! YUMMY !!!!!! The legumes was amazing because it didn‚Äôt have too much acid in it. Some places love to add acid or too much spice to the legumes but this one was perfect! The rice was amazing also because it was fully cooked. I really don‚Äôt like ordering this kind of dish or ANY and Haitian food that is not fully cooked! I applaud this place!

I rarely write reviews but when I do it‚Äôs serious! I would like to also say I applaud the owner for believing in him and hiring him. This man will go far in life. Please continue to support employees like him. I have to also give a round of applause to the people in the back who put their work in making the food as well. I just can‚Äôt write this review and forget the employees in the back. They are part of the business as well! It‚Äôs not easy waking up everyday cooking and serving people - it can be challenging. I applaud this place. For such a small place to eat-the service and food is amazing! This goes to say never judge a book by its cover. You never know the greatness it has.

Please continue to do well in the community. I appreciate your business!

Sincerely,

A loyal customer

title: Chinese Dragon
text:
Recently, I ordered delivery food from Chinese Dragon. I had zero expectations (either way) for their food; it was late, but their kitchen was open and they were willing to deliver to my slightly out-of-range location for a small, additional delivery fee. (A paltry $ amount, compared to the ridiculous/endless delivery and service fees Uber Cheats, Grub Nub, etc. tack on to every order.)

45 minutes later, my food arrived -- and it was wonderful! Creamy egg drop soup; perfect saucy chicken saut√©ed to perfection with a colorful mix of tasty chinese vegetables; delicious chicken fried rice (replete with real, large chunks of meat throughout); admidst this abundance though the rich, tender beef teriaki skewers were actually the first thing to be devoured. (I would usually save one for later but hey...life is short and their siren song called me.) So good!

In summary, I still can't believe that I polished off so much food, so easily at 1am...or that there were so many (non-teriaki) leftovers the next day. A++ service and food, I highly recommend Chinese Dragon!

Service: Felt rushed, and oddly uncomfortable. They treated me as if I was going to steal something constantly asking me if I was ready to order. Again, first time here so I was reading the menu. The clerk came from behind the counter to stand by me with his hands in his pocket until I ordered.

title: Saigon Hut
text: It saddens me to write this review, I really enjoy this restaurants' food and atmosphere; it is very homey. However I just want other customers to know to be wary when ordering take out. It happened twice to me. The restaurant uses a website called Skipli which uses Doordash as third party. If your order is lost or damaged, the restaurant will do never about it and tells you to contact the driver or website. Doordash can't do anything either.  Skipli does not even have a way to contact them since it is a marketing site. The first time the restaurant forgot the added veggies I had paid for. Since it was 5 dollars and I just brushed it off. The second time the driver had taken my drinks. Please do not use their skipli website to order food.

title: Saigon Hut
text:
We ordered three different bowls of pho and they were mediocre at best; a little bland for our taste and lacked the aromatics and depth of flavor.  Could have also been because it was dinner time and the broth wasn't as fresh.  The atmosphere was what you would expect from a hole in the wall restaurant.  The service was bad.  We ordered Goi Ga (salad w/ chicken) as our appetizer and never got it.  We never got waters or even offered if we wanted drinks.  They didn't know what fish sauce was so definitely no Vietnamese working that evening.  After 3 tries, he did eventually figure out what we were asking for.  Our server seemed to be hiding in the kitchen most of the time.  We waited a long time after finishing our food before I had to go back there to get him to get our bill.  Friendly but not a good server.
Based on the other reviews, maybe everything would have been better if the owners were there.  Definitely better places in Boston.

title: Rino's Place
text:
BEWARE OF THE SECRET RESERVATION LIST!!

It is very well advertised that this is a ‚Äúno reservations taken‚Äù restaurant. We learned the hard way that you actually CAN make reservations (by emailing the owner directly).

So, when we put our name in for a group of 4 at 6:30 pm and the hostess told us there were only 3 tables ahead of us, we were more than happy to wait as we had been wanting to try this spot for a long time. 2 hours after patiently waiting outdoors (you can‚Äôt wait indoors here), and after watching many groups stroll in to their RESERVED tables, we decided to check in with the hostess. Her advice was that we should have made a reservation by contacting the owner directly.

So, if you find yourself waiting for a table here, just know that the empty table you see through the window may just remain empty until a limo full of people with a secret reservation arrives for their 8:15 reservation.

Easy fix: instead of leading on to your customers that they are the third ones in line for a table, tell them the truth (we have some large parties tonight, special event or request, etc). If we knew the truth, we would have simply returned another night. Alas, our patience did not prevail and we gave up at the 2 hour mark.

text:
**UPDATED - PLEASE READ FULL REVIEW**

ORIGINAL:
Please, either: 1. Answer your phone, or; 2. Update the information on your website/Google search to reflect if you are either permanently closed or have hours alternative to those posted. It's ignorant and neglectful to simply leave it as is AND have no answer to phone calls. If anyone knows the status of this restaurant, please advise. Thank you.

**************

UPDATE:
Although still confused and disappointed that I could not get a phone answered before heading to Luna's - once we arrived we were treated very well. Every accommodation was made to service us to our liking. The foods were varied, fresh and delicious!! You could tell the chef and staff take great care and pride. The place is IMMACULATE!! A must for me when dining out. I loved the Latin cuisine infusion to traditional dishes. The servings were ample enough by my measure [I'm not a glutton and understand portion control] and aside from being delicious everything was fresh and prepared to order. Unlike many who commented here, we did not find rude, neglectful staff on hand; nor did we find the prices outrageous for these "Biden's - Build Back Better" out of control inflationary times. If they put on a general recording on the phone to answer FAQ, this would be a huge help. But answering the phone is even better!! We merely needed to know if they in fact were OPEN and hadn't succumbed to a Biden Administration induced demise. We were happy to learn they hadn't!! Thank you for excellent food, outstanding service and affordable prices!!

text: Food was decent, but everyone in my party left with a bad taste in their mouths after we were very rudely chastised and lectured about asking to split the check by our waiter, who was clearly having a bad night even though he already had his mandatory 20% gratuity added into the nearly $900 bill from our table. It might be annoying to you, but if the paying customer asks to split the bill at the end of the meal, you should smile and do it without complaining and making everyone feel awkward. Splitting a bill is a basic part of being a server; if you can‚Äôt manage it without fussing I suggest getting a different gig.

title: Rail Stop Restaurant & Bar
text:
EDIT: The manager reached out and compensated our meal from our last visit‚Äîwe returned for lunch and had a pleasant meal. The service was attentive, kind, and more readily available than our previous visits. The food was also much better and everything was properly cooked.

Twice is not always nice. Just like the first time we visited the service remains extremely slow from the moment we walked through the door to when we recieved our check and the food is still very poorly done. Brunch came out cold and every egg we orded was very overcooked‚Äîvery overpriced for the quality. Also, the hot sauce only comes in miniature doll house sizes. At least our server was friendly when we could find her. It's embarrassing that the Rail Stop continues to have this problem a year after our first visit. The manager should be fired or the place should be submitted to Kitchen Nightmares. If Gordon Ramsay turned the place around, we might consider a third visit. Until then, stear clear Boston.

title: Saltie Girl
text: Came for the seafood but stayed for the cocktails and chill vibes. We sat at bar so did not get a chance to get familiar with menu or hear about dishes. The oysters were great! title: Saltie Girl
text:
I post a review on Google only for something exceptionally good or exceptionally bad; unfortunately, Saltie Girl was the latter.

I wanted a quick clam chowder lunch before heading home, and Saltie Girl had been mentioned more than once as making a good one. What a disappointment! It was over-thickened, over-salted, under-clammed, and for some odd reason served topped by two fried clams with breading that had already turned soggy.

And speaking of soggy, the French fries were limp as can be. They were listed on the menu as having black garlic and truffle, but truffle flavor (truffle salt?) was all I could taste. I did see some black specs, which I hoped and assumed were some sort of edible item, but otherwise the garlic was absent.

The host was courteous and helpful (this was the only reason I gave two stars instead of one), but the server committed a major faux pas for a higher-end restaurant by not asking, after I ate only half of the chowder and maybe a quarter of the fries, if I was unhappy with the food.

I also ordered a shiso cocktail, which tasted mostly of citrus and sugar, a little bit of gin, and not at all of shiso except for one tired leaf affixed to the glass by an adorable little clothespin.

My husband is a black man who was wearing jeans and a black hooded sweatshirt.  We order pickup through Grubhub a lot as we don't dine-in due to my husband's health issues. As good as the food is, as we have eaten Carlos' meals throughout the years, this leaves a horrible taste in our mouths and a horrible feeling in our hearts.
